Don't get me started on his morality blah blah blah.  Put simply, 95% of the past presidents were scoundrels and flawed men in their own way (exept maybe Jimmy Carter, who was nice guy but just wasn't good prez)  Our past presidents were Alcoholics (list goes on), adulterers (reagan, kennedy, clinton, johnson, etc...etc..etc..etc.), pot smokers (bush, clinton), slave owners (pre-civil war prez), cocaine users (bush), etc...etc.  <br>
<br>
As for the economy, deficits suck because a) it impacts consumer confidence, b) effects terms of deals we get with other countries, and c) forces govt. services to be cut in order to balance the budget.<br>
<br>
Put simply, consumers and investors hate the word &quot;deficit&quot;.  When they hear it, they don't invest, don't buy things, don't travel.  This on a whole has devastating effects on the economy.  Investors and consumers are like sheep.  They get nervous easy, and run for the hills at the sign of trouble.  Deficits are a sign of trouble.  During the Clinton years this country saw amazing amounts of consumer spending and investing.  One reason for this was a balanced budget, as consumers were happy that the U.S. had a balanced budget.<br>
<br>
Deficits also effects the U.S. credit rating I believe.  Therefore large international deals hinge on the deficits.  International goods and services become even more expensive when the U.S. has a high deficit.<br>
<br>
Finally, deficits mean slashed govt. services.  Now republicans like this, that is why most republicans don't care about deficits.  Republicans main strategy is to rack up huge deficits, and then say &quot;oh well..time to cut social security, medicare, legal services, and other services to balance the budget!&quot;.  What republicans don't realize is that their slash and burn tactics, coupled with &quot;vodoo economics&quot; i.e., trickle down economics, i.e., tax breaks for rich, just shatters consumer confidence.  Shattered consumer confidence = recession.<br>
