<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373618" target="top">Wheee what fun EZCodes are!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 480<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/20/03 1:30:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clinton Speaks</span><hr size=1> I think it's kind of funny that people are so against tax breaks.  &quot;They help the rich and not the poor!&quot;  Well, no crap.  Who pays the vast majority of taxes?  The rich!  If they pay the most taxes, then they SHOULD gain the most benefit from tax breaks.<br>
<br>
Kerridwyn hit the nail on the head.  When Reagan was president, he inspired confidence.  People spent money.  As a result, people earned more money.  As a result of that, the government brought in more revenue.<br>
<br>
But in Congress, where real fiscal policy is made, the increase in spending outpaced the increase in revenue.  This caused an even bigger deficit, which in turn increased the national debt.<br>
<br>
In order to get rid of deficit, revenue must increase, and spending must decrease.  No one ever disputes the first condition.  It is merely the how that is debated.  Liberals, as a whole, believe an increase in taxes is the way to go.<br>
<br>
However, conservatives, as a whole, believe cutting taxes can accomplish this even better.  The theory is that by letting the taxpayers keep more of THEIR money that THEY earned, then more money will filter around the economy.  People will buy more, etc.<br>
<br>
It works.  But the problem comes when that second condition is not met.  Spending must be controlled.  If it grows, then we are in the same boat as before.  And if it grows too much in relation to revenue, then we are worse off than before.<br>
<br>
Our economy's health comes when money changes hands.  Increasing taxes causes people to hoard money.  Lowering taxes allows people to spend more, increasing cash flow, and the health of our consumer-driven economy.<br>
<br>
So, to sum up and get back on topic, why the hell should I care what Bill Clinton says?  He's no longer President, and my opinion matters just as much as his. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showMessageRange?topicID=332.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showMessageRange?topicID=332.topic&start=41&stop=45>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showPrevMessage?topicID=332.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showNextMessage?topicID=332.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.threadControl?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4"